{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"All direct and transitive dependencies are extracted from the manifest and included in the vulnerability check.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is module handoff: manifest parser/resolver output must flow into the vulnerability-check input set. A pure Unit test on one parser function can miss dropped transitive deps at wiring boundaries (MOCK-MISS). System was considered and rejected because the behavior text is about extraction/inclusion, not real network/OS/subprocess behavior; a stubbed vuln API can still expose missing dependencies (REJECTION-GATE).","test_description":"Use fixture manifests/lockfiles with known direct+transitive trees, run the extraction + check-request assembly path end-to-end in-process, and assert every expected dependency appears in the query payload captured by a fake API client.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The vulnerability database query returns results that match the exact version ranges in the manifest, not just the package name.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a deterministic external API contract risk: version-range semantics can differ from local assumptions, and mocks can hide real mismatch behavior (REAL-INFRA, MOCK-HIDE). Agentic was considered and rejected because this is not model-judgment quality; it is deterministic query/filter behavior (REJECTION-GATE).","test_description":"Against a real vulnerability DB API (or real staging instance), submit manifests containing same package names with differing version ranges and assert returned CVEs map only to the exact vulnerable ranges requested.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.62,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The severity sorting places Critical above High above Medium above Low, with CVEs of the same severity sorted by CVSS score.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic comparator logic within a local function/object boundary, with no required module wiring or external I/O. Higher levels were considered and rejected because behavior text is only sort ordering rules, not integration/system concerns (REJECTION-GATE).","test_description":"Call the sort function with unsorted CVE fixtures spanning all severities and equal-severity CVSS ties; assert exact ordered output sequence.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The manifest modification changes only the affected dependency's version, leaving all other entries unchanged.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failures commonly appear across parser/updater/serializer boundaries (e.g., unrelated entries rewritten). A single-function Unit test can miss these cross-module mutation effects (MOCK-MISS). System was considered and rejected because real OS/network/subprocess is not required to detect unintended entry changes; in-process file/module wiring is enough (REJECTION-GATE).","test_description":"Run manifest read/modify/write through the real local modules on fixture files, then compare parsed structures and textual diff to verify exactly one dependency version changed and all other keys/values remained identical.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The auto-generated pull request is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires real repository PR creation, which crosses real HTTP/API boundaries and remote side effects (REAL-INFRA). Integration with mocks can pass while auth/branch/PR/diff contract failures occur in reality (MOCK-HIDE). Workflow was considered and rejected because no multi-step agentic chain is required by this behavior text (REJECTION-GATE).","test_description":"Run scanner against a real test repository, trigger one critical vuln, and assert a real PR is opened with exactly one dependency-version change in the diff and correct branch metadata.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.84,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is local semver comparison logic, deterministic and isolated. No external I/O or module orchestration is required to reveal incorrect major-bump detection. Higher levels were considered and rejected because behavior text is strictly comparison correctness (REJECTION-GATE).","test_description":"Test semver comparison function with representative version pairs (including pre-release/build metadata) and assert breaking=true only for major-version increments per semver rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.88,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is orchestration between semver decision, PR creation gate, and output/reporting modules. Unit tests on each piece can miss incorrect wiring (e.g., flag set but PR still attempted). System was considered and rejected because behavior can be validated with in-process wiring and a fake PR client; real network is not required by the behavior text (REJECTION-GATE).","test_description":"Execute scan flow with a fixture vulnerability requiring major bump; assert PR client is not invoked and scanner output includes the explicit review-required flag/state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
